body: I watched The Imitation Game. I read up a little bit on the events before and after to give me some context. I think the movie was a very dramatized version of the events based on what I read about German WW2 encryption, such as that the Polish had decrypted Enigma messages in 1938. However I enjoyed the movie and the interesting personal stories of the people involved. I think it relates to this class because Alan Turing's work is the basis for a programmable computer and his theories provided the basis for a lot of what we learned in the class. I read that the German navy implemented a different version of the Enigma machine at one point that interrupted the British ability to read their communications. I thought that was also interesting and could have been interesting to see in the movie.
